<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910627-0030</DOCNO><DOCID>910627-0030.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Lasmo Canada Inc.:   Firm to Buy Petro-Canada's   Interest in Alberta Oil Field</HL><DATE>06/27/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7</SO><CO>   T.LMO</CO><MS>ENERGY (ENE)</MS><IN>OIL, SECONDARY (OIS)PETROLEUM (PET)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>CANADA (CN)NORTH AMERICA (NME)</RE><LP>   Lasmo Canada Inc. said it agreed in principle to purchasePetro-Canada's interest in an Alberta oil field for 43.6million Canadian dollars (US$38.2 million).   A spokesman for Canadian government-controlledPetro-Canada, of which 15% was sold in an initial publicoffering this month, confirmed the sale of its 12.7% workinginterest in the Nipisi field, but wouldn't comment further.</LP><TEXT>   Both energy companies are based in Calgary, Alberta.   Lasmo said it would pay C$8.7 million of the purchaseprice, to be financed with bank debt. It said the balancewould be provided through an unnamed financial institution.Lasmo officials couldn't be reached to comment.   Lasmo, which already owns about 6% of the Nipisi field,said the acquisition would add 2.3 million barrels of oil andnatural gas liquids to the company's reserve base, whichcurrently stands at 30 million barrels. Lasmo also hasreserves of about 48 billion cubic feet of natural gas.</TEXT></DOC>